data.description: Seize this once-in-a-lifetime opportunity to own a truly timeless masterpiece, an exquisitely renovated 1840s Antebellum luxury home on the picturesque Country Club Road in LaGrange, Georgia. Being one of the few homes of its age in the area, it offers a unique history as it was moved piece by piece and reinforced with steel beams and concrete blocks from its original location to where it stands now, a magnificent fixture in the charming city of LaGrange. The wow-factor hits you the moment you pull onto the circular drive. 6 wooden columns welcome you to the estate in a grand fashion. The grandeur continues when you walk in the door, with a breathtaking foyer flanked by a gorgeous formal living room and a separate dining room, each complete with their own fireplaces and unique mantles, made from the first and second steps from an French alter. Continue into the breakfast room and living room, which share an additional fireplace. The kitchen has been completely renovated with stylistic influences from a Mexican Hacienda, like the massive pine table and pantry, which date back more than 100 years. White marble countertops and backsplash combine with stainless steel Viking appliances to guarantee that whoever cooks in this kitchen won't miss out on any functionality. The kitchen extends with a butler's pantry area, complete with extra counterspace, massive China cabinet, washer/dryer, and additional oversized stainless steel sink and additional dishwasher to match the main kitchen area. This extra space truly completes the entertainer's dream kitchen. A stunning master bedroom rounds out the main floor, with a gorgeously renovated bathroom and nearby half bath. Going upstairs, you're welcomed with a beautiful gallery area, serving as an additional entertaining space with access to the column-adorned balcony on the front home. Surrounding the gallery area, you'll find 3 ornate bedrooms, 2 renovated full bathrooms, and a spacious office. This one-of-a-kind home was renovated and interiorly designed by the current owner and interior designer, Oliver Carballo.  The luxury continues outside of the home with a gate providing entry to a detached garage and a stunning courtyard. Enjoy the gorgeous landscaped yards and very well-maintained English Garden, complete with a gazebo. All of this luxury and beauty just minutes from the shops and restaurants of Downtown LaGrange. Furniture and decorations are available for purchase via a separate bill of sale, making this masterpiece completely move-in ready just for you.
